derives the balmy pill Its virtues , the physician skill : That over each act and thought presides , Directs his hand , his counsel guides : Else medicine's unavailing store Shall vainly glide through every poor , Through every poor the mineral rill In vain its gifted powers instill
another's brow : Health I entreat ; whose jocund throng Wantons each laughing grace among ; With Health the dancing minutes crowned , The field of all my wishes bound
